WEBVTT

00:05.222 --> 00:08.008
Eddie: I got a call from
the person who hit me.

00:08.051 --> 00:10.184
When my husband's upset,
he lashes out.

00:10.227 --> 00:12.708
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:12.751 --> 00:14.710
It wasn't a guy that I dated
after my divorce.

00:14.753 --> 00:16.190
It was a woman.

00:16.233 --> 00:17.887
Austin: You don't pull a film
from a festival.

00:17.930 --> 00:19.889
You show it and get
the whole town talking.

00:19.932 --> 00:21.282
It just feels like
a catch-and-kill.

00:21.325 --> 00:23.197
I'm sorry.

00:23.240 --> 00:24.981
Tomorrow, we get the results
back from audience testing.Okay.

00:25.025 --> 00:26.896
I'll be curious to see
what the results say

00:26.939 --> 00:29.029
about how you are
at talking topeople

00:29.072 --> 00:30.813
instead of
talking aboutthem.

00:30.856 --> 00:32.293
I want to own
my own place someday,

00:32.336 --> 00:33.772
so I never have to work
for someone.

00:33.816 --> 00:35.209
It's one of the perks
I'll miss.

00:35.252 --> 00:37.124
If Peter's in a coma,
then he didn't hear

00:37.167 --> 00:38.908
what I said to him
on Maggie's podcast.

00:38.951 --> 00:40.823
And now I don't know
if he ever will.

00:40.866 --> 00:42.259
Gary: Detective
was following me.

00:42.303 --> 00:43.869
How do you know
he didn't follow you here?

00:43.913 --> 00:45.132
He's caught up with
something else.

00:45.175 --> 00:46.220
Peter's awake.

00:46.263 --> 00:47.395
Hello?
Peter: It's Peter.

00:47.438 --> 00:48.613
I know it was you.

00:48.657 --> 00:49.832
♪♪

00:51.138 --> 00:54.054
Your vitals look great.
Blood work as well.

00:54.097 --> 00:55.925
How are the headaches?Um, much better.

00:55.968 --> 00:56.708
Thank you.
Yeah.

00:56.752 --> 00:57.753
And your memory?

00:57.796 --> 00:59.755
Still a little foggy,

00:59.798 --> 01:04.890
but I remember
your name -- Eileen.

01:04.934 --> 01:07.893
That's cheating,
but I'll allow it.

01:07.937 --> 01:09.939
Your husband is,
uh, quite the charmer.

01:09.982 --> 01:14.248
Mm-hmm. Um,
he can come home today, yes?

01:14.291 --> 01:15.553
Absolutely.

01:15.597 --> 01:16.815
As long as he has someone
to keep an eye on him.

01:16.859 --> 01:17.903
Yeah.

01:17.947 --> 01:18.948
If you'd like to
come with me,

01:18.991 --> 01:20.645
I'll go over
his list of medications.

01:20.689 --> 01:23.126
Great.Thank you so much.

01:23.170 --> 01:26.042
So, I just had
some questions.Uh-huh.

01:26.086 --> 01:27.130
In the morning,
he tends to get a little bit...

01:27.174 --> 01:33.571
♪♪

01:33.615 --> 01:35.356
Gary: Flower delivery.

01:35.399 --> 01:37.488
♪♪

01:37.532 --> 01:38.446
[ Door closes ]

01:38.489 --> 01:43.146
♪♪

01:43.190 --> 01:45.017
I didn't, uh --
didn't think you'd come.

01:45.061 --> 01:46.715
You wanna tell me
what I'm doing here?

01:46.758 --> 01:48.543
I mean,
I think you know.

01:48.586 --> 01:51.111
Or do you not remember putting
a bag over my head,

01:51.154 --> 01:52.590
dragging me into
my music studio,

01:52.634 --> 01:54.157
and tying me to
a chair?

01:54.201 --> 01:56.638
♪♪

01:56.681 --> 01:58.770
But maybe
your friend Christopher

01:58.814 --> 02:01.208
could refresh
your memory?

02:01.251 --> 02:02.948
♪♪

02:02.992 --> 02:05.125
If your memory is so great,
why --

02:05.168 --> 02:06.604
why are you talking to me
and not the police?

02:06.648 --> 02:08.389
No, I have been.

02:08.432 --> 02:10.695
They've asked me all kinds of
questions about that night,

02:10.739 --> 02:14.221
and I have told them that
I don't remember anything.

02:14.264 --> 02:16.179
Doctor says that
that can happen sometimes

02:16.223 --> 02:17.789
with head trauma.

02:17.833 --> 02:19.182
♪♪

02:19.226 --> 02:23.752
But sometimes,
the memories can come back.

02:23.795 --> 02:28.365
We just have no way
of predicting when.

02:28.409 --> 02:29.932
What do you want?

02:29.975 --> 02:32.456
Sophie recorded a podcast,
accusing me of things --

02:32.500 --> 02:33.892
Things you did.

02:33.936 --> 02:35.807
I want you to get her
to take it down.

02:35.851 --> 02:37.418
It's too late for that.

02:37.461 --> 02:39.071
Hundreds of people
have heard it already.

02:39.115 --> 02:41.204
And all of those people
will think

02:41.248 --> 02:42.423
that she's taking it down

02:42.466 --> 02:44.599
because she's not telling
the truth.

02:44.642 --> 02:46.078
If you can get her
to do that...

02:46.122 --> 02:48.864
♪♪

02:48.907 --> 02:50.866
...maybe my memory
never comes back.

02:50.909 --> 02:53.390
♪♪

02:53.434 --> 02:55.218
Call the police.

02:55.262 --> 02:56.567
Tell them
whatever you want.

02:56.611 --> 02:58.787
♪♪

02:58.830 --> 03:01.355
I got nothing left
to lose.

03:01.398 --> 03:02.530
♪♪

03:02.573 --> 03:05.272
[ Door opens, closes ]

03:05.315 --> 03:07.317
♪♪

03:12.844 --> 03:14.194
You think you can
get away with that,

03:14.237 --> 03:15.499
you got
another think coming.

03:15.543 --> 03:17.719
You ain't gonna punk me.[ Cellphone beeps ]

03:17.762 --> 03:19.199
What's going on?

03:19.242 --> 03:21.723
I'm just deleting Paragon Plus
from all of our devices.

03:21.766 --> 03:24.204
Gonna shelve my movie,
you lose my $7.99 a month.

03:24.247 --> 03:25.379
Okay.

03:25.422 --> 03:27.250
Uh...

03:27.294 --> 03:29.470
Look at that.

03:29.513 --> 03:31.385
We said we wanted to
read more anyway.

03:31.428 --> 03:32.516
Checkmate.
Boom.

03:33.865 --> 03:35.040
Wanna call in sick today?

03:35.084 --> 03:36.085
'Cause I know something
that we can do

03:36.128 --> 03:37.434
that doesn't involve
Paragon Plus.

03:37.478 --> 03:39.349
Ooh, I would love to,

03:39.393 --> 03:40.829
but I can't
do that to Valerie.

03:40.872 --> 03:42.309
We have
three birthday parties today,

03:42.352 --> 03:45.616
and our manager-in-chief
Gerald is very specific

03:45.660 --> 03:47.270
about the way
we serve cake.

03:47.314 --> 03:48.271
[ FaceTime ringing ]I'm guessing
because no one

03:48.315 --> 03:49.838
attended his parties
as a child.

03:49.881 --> 03:51.100
Uh, it's my dad.
Why did you have to

03:51.143 --> 03:52.493
show him
how to video chat?

03:52.536 --> 03:53.929
He better have
his pants on.

03:53.972 --> 03:55.757
I can't unsee what I saw
the last time he hit me up.

03:55.800 --> 03:57.280
[ Chuckles ]
Good luck with that.

03:57.324 --> 03:58.368
Mm.
Mm.

03:58.412 --> 03:59.282
I blame you for this.

03:59.326 --> 04:01.328
[ Ringing stops ]

04:01.371 --> 04:02.807
Hey, Pop.[ Door closes ]

04:02.851 --> 04:05.245
Can't tell you how good it is
to see your face.

04:05.288 --> 04:06.550
What's up? I've been thinking about

04:06.594 --> 04:08.596
what happened to you
with the movie.

04:08.639 --> 04:10.772
You got a raw deal, son.

04:10.815 --> 04:12.382
So I thought you should come to
church with me and --

04:12.426 --> 04:14.602
Dad, how many times
do I have to tell you?

04:14.645 --> 04:16.821
Church doesn't work for me
the way it works for you.

04:16.865 --> 04:18.606
If you would
let me finish...

04:18.649 --> 04:20.869
I'm in a men's group
that meets on Wednesdays.

04:20.912 --> 04:23.654
We're supposed to be doing
bible study, but mostly,

04:23.698 --> 04:26.222
we just sit around
and swap war stories.

04:26.266 --> 04:29.007
I thought maybe today,
I'd show them your film.

04:29.051 --> 04:30.879
Brag about my son
to a few friends.

04:30.922 --> 04:34.361
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

04:34.404 --> 04:35.536
Well, I guess
it would be nice

04:35.579 --> 04:37.407
for somebody
to see my film.

04:37.451 --> 04:38.408
What time
should I be there?

04:38.452 --> 04:40.236
Showtime's at noon.

04:40.280 --> 04:43.239
Oh, and it's BYOB --

04:43.283 --> 04:45.633
Bring Your Own Bible.

04:45.676 --> 04:47.330
No, don't -- don't get up!
Da--

04:47.374 --> 04:49.593
[ Phone thumps on table ]It's not JunkTime,
Pops.

04:49.637 --> 04:51.552
That is not photogenic.

04:51.595 --> 04:53.380
I swear, Mom is getting
way too comfortable

04:53.423 --> 04:54.859
having a gay son.
[ Chuckles ]

04:54.903 --> 04:56.165
You know, this morning,
she asked me

04:56.208 --> 04:58.472
if her jeans
made her butt look cute.

04:58.515 --> 05:00.212
[ Chuckling ]
She did not!

05:00.256 --> 05:02.040
Luckily, I was eating
a croissant,

05:02.084 --> 05:03.955
so I stuffed
the rest of it in my mouth

05:03.999 --> 05:05.348
and then pretended
I was choking.

05:05.392 --> 05:06.915
[ Laughs]
Let's just say,

05:06.958 --> 05:08.917
you owe me for all the therapy
I'm gonna need someday.

05:08.960 --> 05:12.007
[ Chuckles ]
Just add it to my tab.

05:12.050 --> 05:14.792
Or you can
pay me back now.

05:14.836 --> 05:16.403
Today is Milo's birthday,

05:16.446 --> 05:19.928
and I'm staying up late for
a video date to celebrate,

05:19.971 --> 05:24.976
and my amazing sister
is going to personally deliver

05:25.020 --> 05:26.848
his birthday gift
to him.

05:26.891 --> 05:28.719
Okay, fine.

05:28.763 --> 05:29.894
It'll be like
I'm actually there.

05:29.938 --> 05:32.854
[ Chuckles ]
Well, I wish you were.

05:32.897 --> 05:34.421
I miss you.

05:34.464 --> 05:36.336
I miss you, too.

05:37.206 --> 05:40.383
Hey, I, um --
I listened to your podcast.

05:40.427 --> 05:42.777
What you said
was really brave.

05:42.820 --> 05:46.563
I think it's gonna make a lot of
people feel less alone.

05:46.607 --> 05:48.043
Thank you.
[ Chuckles softly]

05:49.305 --> 05:50.611
Now, can I ask you
something?

05:50.654 --> 05:52.656
Yeah. Anything.

05:52.700 --> 05:55.006
I need you to be
totally honest, alright?

05:55.050 --> 05:56.225
Okay.

05:56.268 --> 05:57.574
Okay.

06:00.055 --> 06:01.317
Uh, do these jeans
make my butt look cute?

06:01.361 --> 06:03.885
[ Laughs ]

06:03.928 --> 06:05.452
[ Laughs ]
My eyes!

06:05.495 --> 06:11.806
♪♪

06:11.849 --> 06:13.764
[ Dialing ]

06:13.808 --> 06:14.983
[ Line ringing]

06:15.026 --> 06:17.377
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

06:18.465 --> 06:19.422
How'd it go?

06:19.466 --> 06:21.163
Not good.

06:21.206 --> 06:22.512
He remembers everything.

06:22.556 --> 06:28.649
♪♪

06:28.692 --> 06:30.390
What does he want?

06:30.433 --> 06:33.784
He wanted me to get Sophie
to take down her podcast

06:33.828 --> 06:35.612
in exchange
for his silence.

06:35.656 --> 06:37.527
♪♪

06:37.571 --> 06:38.702
You're not doing that.

06:40.138 --> 06:42.445
I think we'd both better start
looking for a lawyer.

06:42.489 --> 06:47.450
♪♪

06:47.494 --> 06:54.065
♪♪

06:54.109 --> 06:56.503
Thanks again for taking Theo
to the water park today.

06:56.546 --> 06:58.026
[ Speaking Korean ]

06:58.069 --> 07:00.115
Make sure he has an hour
to digest his lunch

07:00.158 --> 07:02.204
before he goes on
the water slide.

07:02.247 --> 07:03.945
I learned that last time
the hard way.

07:03.988 --> 07:06.730
And I'll see you back here
for dinner,

07:06.774 --> 07:10.255
as long as I can dig out
from under these contracts.

07:10.299 --> 07:13.911
[ Speaking Korean ]

07:13.955 --> 07:17.828
Oh? And how is
Randy Kwan's mother?

07:17.872 --> 07:19.656
[ Speaking Korean ]
Hmm.

07:19.700 --> 07:22.877
[ Speaking Korean ]

07:22.920 --> 07:25.183
I'm surprised
Randy's still single.

07:25.227 --> 07:27.011
He's had everyone's mother
pushing him on them

07:27.055 --> 07:28.448
since junior high.

07:28.491 --> 07:31.233
He's a very successful
doctor.

07:31.276 --> 07:32.974
He's not a doctor,
he's a dentist.

07:33.017 --> 07:34.541
[ Sighs ]

07:34.584 --> 07:38.980
[ Speaking Korean ]

07:39.023 --> 07:44.725
No, Mom, what I "should" do
is what's right for me,

07:44.768 --> 07:46.074
and that's not
Randy Kwan.

07:47.075 --> 07:49.643
I just don't want you
to be alone.

07:49.686 --> 07:51.949
Actually, being alone
sounds amazing right now.

07:51.993 --> 07:53.516
[ Sighs ]

07:53.560 --> 07:54.474
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

07:54.517 --> 07:55.779
[ Speaking Korean ]

07:55.823 --> 07:57.085
[ Vibrating stops ]

07:57.128 --> 07:58.869
Hey, Darcy.

07:58.913 --> 08:01.002
No, you are calling
at the perfect time.

08:03.874 --> 08:05.136
What-- What's going on?

08:06.573 --> 08:09.837
[ Sighs ] You know, when I asked
to see your new place,

08:09.880 --> 08:11.142
I wasn't volunteering
my services

08:11.186 --> 08:12.840
as a human hand truck.

08:12.883 --> 08:14.145
Ah. You know,
I see you more as

08:14.189 --> 08:16.321
a whiny roller skate,
but your point is taken.

08:16.365 --> 08:18.759
[ Chuckles ] Whoa.

08:18.802 --> 08:20.195
When I told you to get a job,
I didn't think

08:20.238 --> 08:23.154
it'd be dancing at that
strip club out by the airport.

08:23.198 --> 08:25.243
Tell Destiny
I said wazzaaaa.

08:27.028 --> 08:29.552
I went to see
the woman who hit me.

08:29.596 --> 08:31.598
She left that for me
before I knew she was gone.

08:31.641 --> 08:34.078
[ Papers thump lightly ]That's an expensive
cup of coffee.

08:34.122 --> 08:36.472
$7,500.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.779
To try to take the sting
out of never walking again.

08:38.822 --> 08:40.128
Sounds like
it didn't work.

08:40.171 --> 08:41.869
Well, if I keep it,
I feel like

08:41.912 --> 08:43.523
I'm accepting an apology
for what she did,

08:43.566 --> 08:44.567
and I can't do that.

08:44.611 --> 08:45.742
I get that.

08:45.786 --> 08:49.398
And she told me
she was distracted

08:49.441 --> 08:51.748
because her husband
was drinking that night,

08:51.792 --> 08:53.837
and when he drinks,
he does bad things.

08:53.881 --> 08:56.666
Yeah, it's almost poetic.

08:56.710 --> 08:59.539
Well, I understand if you decide
not to keep the money.

08:59.582 --> 09:01.062
But if you do,

09:01.105 --> 09:02.846
I should probably get 10%
for helping you move.

09:02.890 --> 09:04.282
Stop by the club
this weekend.

09:04.326 --> 09:06.589
Destiny and I will take you to
the Champagne Room,

09:06.633 --> 09:07.895
hook you right up.

09:07.938 --> 09:09.113
Dude, I live in
the Champagne Room.

09:09.157 --> 09:12.421
[ Chuckles ][ Cellphone vibrating ]

09:12.464 --> 09:13.465
[ Vibrating stops ]

09:13.509 --> 09:14.858
Hey, everything okay?

09:14.902 --> 09:17.382
Did you know Gary and Darcy
broke up?

09:17.426 --> 09:18.688
What?

09:18.732 --> 09:20.603
She just called me
on her way to Lenox.

09:20.647 --> 09:23.432
She was really upset.

09:23.475 --> 09:24.912
Well, what happened?

09:24.955 --> 09:27.131
Apparently, Gary said
he couldn't leave his friends.

09:27.175 --> 09:29.960
♪♪

09:30.004 --> 09:31.832
Trina: The doctors think
we caught it early,

09:31.875 --> 09:33.529
but my head's
just been spinning

09:33.573 --> 09:35.357
ever since I found out,

09:35.400 --> 09:37.098
and now they're putting
all these treatment plans

09:37.141 --> 09:38.969
in front of me,

09:39.013 --> 09:41.581
but honestly,
I'm really scared.

09:41.624 --> 09:44.061
I haven't even
told my family yet.

09:44.105 --> 09:46.020
It's really scary.
I know.

09:46.063 --> 09:47.412
I've --

09:47.456 --> 09:50.328
I mean, eh,
millions of women

09:50.372 --> 09:53.723
have been where you are
right now.

09:53.767 --> 09:56.030
I would encourage you to find
a breast cancer support group.

09:56.073 --> 09:57.379
If you stay on the line,

09:57.422 --> 09:59.729
my producer will give you
some resources,

09:59.773 --> 10:02.123
and I hope you get the support
you deserve.

10:02.166 --> 10:03.864
Thank you, Dr. Bloom.[ Door opens ]

10:03.907 --> 10:05.866
Man: This has been
"In the Room with Dr. Bloom."

10:05.909 --> 10:07.128
Heard you're getting your
audience testing results today.[ Door closes ]

10:07.171 --> 10:08.172
Yeah.

10:08.216 --> 10:10.566
It was nice knowing you.[ Sighs ]

10:10.610 --> 10:13.308
If it makes you feel any better,
they tested me, too.

10:13.351 --> 10:15.092
They test the traffic
and weather?

10:15.136 --> 10:17.007
No, my sports show.

10:17.051 --> 10:18.922
The one you never heard of
because it went away,

10:18.966 --> 10:20.402
because of the testing.

10:20.445 --> 10:22.273
Oh, that does not
make me feel better.

10:22.317 --> 10:23.361
Jane's a robot.

10:23.405 --> 10:24.841
All she cares about
is numbers.

10:24.885 --> 10:26.582
Honestly, that's a relief,
'cause I'm pretty sure

10:26.626 --> 10:28.628
she hates me
on a personal level.

10:28.671 --> 10:29.977
She used to be
my producer.

10:30.020 --> 10:32.893
She was great...at that.

10:32.936 --> 10:34.590
But then she got promoted,
and not too long after that,

10:34.634 --> 10:36.026
the show was canceled.

10:36.070 --> 10:37.680
She and
her executive cronies said

10:37.724 --> 10:39.073
they were
"trimming the fat."

10:39.116 --> 10:42.032
Like I said...robot.

10:42.076 --> 10:43.338
[ Telephone rings in distance ]

10:43.381 --> 10:45.296
Oh, hello, Jane.

10:45.340 --> 10:47.603
Hi, Nick.

10:47.647 --> 10:49.474
Are you ready to go over
your testing?

10:49.518 --> 10:50.824
Yeah.

10:50.867 --> 10:52.956
Beep-boop-boop,
beep-bop-boop.

10:53.000 --> 10:54.262
[ Door closes ]

10:54.305 --> 10:55.655
♪♪

10:55.698 --> 10:57.308
Dude.
I thought you had

10:57.352 --> 10:58.570
a session today.

10:58.614 --> 11:00.747
You and Darcy broke up?

11:00.790 --> 11:02.139
Ugh.

11:02.183 --> 11:03.619
Yeah.

11:03.663 --> 11:05.534
Yeah, I was gonna
tell you, man.

11:05.577 --> 11:09.103
Uh, I'm not going to Lenox
after all.

11:09.146 --> 11:11.105
Well, what happened?
And give me the truth.[ Refrigerator doors close ]

11:11.148 --> 11:13.716
Not the same BS excuse
Katherine got.

11:13.760 --> 11:14.848
Ed, I-I can't.

11:14.891 --> 11:16.632
Damn it, Gary.
After John died,

11:16.676 --> 11:18.852
you were the one who made us
promise that we would talk.

11:18.895 --> 11:19.983
So talk.

11:20.027 --> 11:21.724
Whatever it is,
we can fix it.

11:21.768 --> 11:28.557
♪♪

11:28.600 --> 11:30.254
Not this one.

11:30.298 --> 11:31.734
♪♪

11:35.912 --> 11:39.046
[ Indistinct conversations ]

11:39.089 --> 11:42.440
♪♪

11:42.484 --> 11:44.486
Dad?
Hey, Pop?

11:44.529 --> 11:46.662
♪♪

11:46.706 --> 11:47.837
Dad.

11:47.881 --> 11:49.970
I thought you said
a few friends.

11:50.013 --> 11:51.580
I did.
Word spread.

11:51.623 --> 11:53.625
Things got out of hand.

11:53.669 --> 11:55.758
Haven't seen this many people
so excited

11:55.802 --> 11:57.499
since Pamela brought in
that slice of toast

11:57.542 --> 11:59.240
she swore had
Jesus' face on it.

11:59.283 --> 12:00.545
You know I-I-I'm not supposed to
show it for this many --

12:00.589 --> 12:03.113
I know, and I don't want you
getting sued.

12:03.157 --> 12:04.898
I'm sorry.

12:04.941 --> 12:06.160
I'll tell them
we're canceling.

12:08.118 --> 12:10.381
I'm really glad
we're seeing this together.

12:10.425 --> 12:13.558
♪♪

12:13.602 --> 12:15.604
Hey, Pop, you know what?

12:15.647 --> 12:16.866
♪♪

12:16.910 --> 12:18.215
Don't do that.

12:18.259 --> 12:20.914
♪♪

12:20.957 --> 12:22.654
We're gonna
show the movie.

12:22.698 --> 12:24.656
What about Paragon Plus?

12:24.700 --> 12:26.441
[ Sucks teeth ]
Let 'em sue me.

12:26.484 --> 12:32.316
♪♪

12:32.360 --> 12:34.101
Unbelievable.

12:35.406 --> 12:38.496
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

12:38.540 --> 12:39.497
[ Vibrating stops ]

12:39.541 --> 12:40.716
Shanice?

12:40.760 --> 12:42.762
I thought
you were shooting today.

12:42.805 --> 12:46.156
Eh, I was, but I just got word
they're pushing my scenes.

12:46.200 --> 12:48.811
Good thing I just spent
two hours in the makeup chair.

12:48.855 --> 12:50.204
What are you up to?

12:50.247 --> 12:52.423
Uh, very exciting things.

12:52.467 --> 12:55.339
I'm, uh, reviewing
form contracts

12:55.383 --> 12:58.299
for a client requesting
an easement adjustment.

12:58.342 --> 13:01.824
Okay. You wanna play hooky
and have lunch again?

13:01.868 --> 13:05.610
Uh, more than
you can imagine. [ Laughs ]

13:05.654 --> 13:08.657
Oh, but Theo's --
Theo's with my mom today.

13:08.700 --> 13:09.876
It's okay.
Kiana's with her dad.

13:09.919 --> 13:12.487
So, it'll just be
the two of us.

13:12.530 --> 13:14.271
Sounds fun.

13:14.315 --> 13:16.230
I'll call Gina and pick up
something from Crocodilze

13:16.273 --> 13:17.666
and bring it over?

13:17.709 --> 13:19.624
Sounds great.
It's a date.

13:19.668 --> 13:21.844
I mean, um, I-I'll --
I'll see you soon.

13:21.888 --> 13:23.672
[ Chuckling ]
I'll see you soon.

13:23.715 --> 13:25.021
Mm...

13:28.242 --> 13:30.592
"I listened to Dr. Bloom
on my commute

13:30.635 --> 13:32.899
and almost fell asleep
at the wheel."

13:32.942 --> 13:34.639
"It's like getting
medical health advice

13:34.683 --> 13:36.554
from
Charlie Brown's teacher."

13:36.598 --> 13:38.295
Ugh.
Are they all this bad?

13:38.339 --> 13:40.123
No, this one's good.

13:40.167 --> 13:43.866
"Dr. Bloom's show
changed my life.

13:43.910 --> 13:46.216
I'm never listening to
talk radio again."

13:46.260 --> 13:50.220
Alright, I get the sense that
you're enjoying this.

13:50.264 --> 13:54.355
I am so sorry
I reported you to HR.

13:54.398 --> 13:55.878
This isn't about that.

13:55.922 --> 13:57.880
Your numbers aren't there.

13:57.924 --> 14:00.361
This afternoon segment
is going to be your last.

14:00.404 --> 14:02.450
♪♪

14:02.493 --> 14:04.844
I'm sorry,
but I'm not surprised.

14:04.887 --> 14:06.584
You never connected
with your audience.

14:06.628 --> 14:08.935
I mean, Dr. Stacy may have given
horrible advice,

14:08.978 --> 14:10.110
but at least people felt like
they were getting

14:10.153 --> 14:14.288
that horrible advice
from their mean aunt.

14:14.331 --> 14:15.942
You know, someone
they could bond with.

14:15.985 --> 14:18.640
As a therapist,
I-I've been trained

14:18.683 --> 14:20.555
to maintain
a professional distance.

14:20.598 --> 14:22.035
Maybe that approach works
in your practice,

14:22.078 --> 14:24.820
but it doesn't work
on the radio.

14:24.864 --> 14:26.996
I mean, you said it yourself on
your first show --

14:27.040 --> 14:28.563
this isn't real therapy.

14:28.606 --> 14:30.782
You're so right.
[ Scoffs ]

14:30.826 --> 14:32.175
I know it's all about numbers
for you,

14:32.219 --> 14:34.917
but I can see why you were
such a great producer.

14:34.961 --> 14:36.788
Who said it was
all about numbers for me?

14:36.832 --> 14:39.052
Um...uh, no one.

14:39.095 --> 14:41.271
It was Nick, wasn't it?

14:41.315 --> 14:42.838
[ Sighs ]

14:42.882 --> 14:45.449
Whoever it was, was probably
just hurt and confused

14:45.493 --> 14:46.711
and maybe felt like

14:46.755 --> 14:48.148
somebody chose a job
over them...

14:49.323 --> 14:50.411
...which isn't even bad.

14:50.454 --> 14:51.542
I mean,
I have done that, too --

14:51.586 --> 14:53.501
Save your advice
for your last show.

14:53.544 --> 14:59.115
♪♪

14:59.159 --> 15:00.638
Why didn't you tell me?

15:00.682 --> 15:03.293
I wanted to tell you.
[ Scoffs ]

15:03.337 --> 15:05.513
Believe me.

15:05.556 --> 15:07.863
I just didn't want to
get you involved.

15:09.343 --> 15:11.606
Okay, wait.

15:11.649 --> 15:13.695
You left
before anything happened.

15:13.738 --> 15:15.044
I mean,
it was that other guy

15:15.088 --> 15:16.828
who put Peter in the hospital,
not you.

15:16.872 --> 15:18.047
The whole night
wouldn't have happened

15:18.091 --> 15:19.962
if it wasn't for me, Ed.

15:20.006 --> 15:22.269
And now Peter's gonna
go to the police,

15:22.312 --> 15:26.490
and Sophie's gonna see
this guy in the news,

15:26.534 --> 15:30.364
and -- and --
and he'll get to play the victim

15:30.407 --> 15:32.627
instead of the bad guy.

15:32.670 --> 15:34.063
Just when she
was finally starting

15:34.107 --> 15:35.456
to get her life
back together.

15:35.499 --> 15:37.937
Hey, it's not great,

15:37.980 --> 15:39.808
but if you really want to
help her,

15:39.851 --> 15:41.331
you need to
get ahead of this.

15:41.375 --> 15:42.854
Trust me.

15:42.898 --> 15:45.205
It will be so much better
if she hears this from you.

15:45.248 --> 15:49.687
♪♪

15:54.127 --> 15:55.824
[ Indistinct conversations ]

15:55.867 --> 15:57.782
What is this?
It smells delicious.

15:57.826 --> 15:59.262
Oh, I thought I'd try
a Bolognese

15:59.306 --> 16:00.829
for a crew meal today.

16:00.872 --> 16:03.440
Don't tell Gerald, but I put in
a whole bottle of red.

16:03.484 --> 16:06.791
Ooh! I guess happy hour's
gonna be extra happy.

16:06.835 --> 16:08.968
Oh, yes.
[ Chuckles ]

16:09.011 --> 16:11.100
To go order for
Shanice Williamson!

16:13.059 --> 16:14.495
Must be weird having
the same name

16:14.538 --> 16:15.800
as a famous movie star.

16:15.844 --> 16:17.541
Oh, no --
Gerald: Hey, guys.

16:17.585 --> 16:19.717
What's with the ketchup
on the side of the plate?

16:19.761 --> 16:21.110
Ketchup goes
in the middle,

16:21.154 --> 16:23.243
in service of both
the steak and the fries.

16:23.286 --> 16:24.984
We have to match
the picture on the menu.

16:25.027 --> 16:26.898
I'm not sure why that's so hard
for you to understand.

16:26.942 --> 16:27.899
Hey, Shanice!

16:27.943 --> 16:29.162
Oh, my God!

16:30.250 --> 16:31.642
Hi.

16:31.686 --> 16:32.817
Sorry to break into
your kitchen,

16:32.861 --> 16:34.254
but I was just
picking up lunch

16:34.297 --> 16:36.734
and asked if I could come
pay compliments to the chef.

16:36.778 --> 16:39.215
Oh, my God.
You're Shanice Williamson.

16:39.259 --> 16:41.609
Uh, just since
I was born.
Heh.

16:41.652 --> 16:44.742
I wanted to say hi to
my dear friend, Regina.

16:44.786 --> 16:45.743
Who I'm sure
you're treating

16:45.787 --> 16:47.876
with all the respect
she deserves,

16:47.919 --> 16:49.834
along with
the rest of your employees.

16:49.878 --> 16:52.272
Oh, yeah. I --
Of -- Of course.

16:54.274 --> 16:55.579
Could I get you
a complimentary T-shirt

16:55.623 --> 16:58.191
from the take-out counter?

16:58.234 --> 17:01.150
I would love that...
Gerald.

17:01.194 --> 17:02.195
Gerald. Yeah.

17:02.238 --> 17:04.327
♪♪

17:04.371 --> 17:06.460
[ Laughs ]Oh. Wow.

17:06.503 --> 17:08.201
Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

17:08.244 --> 17:10.507
I think our lives are gonna get
a lot easier around here.

17:10.551 --> 17:13.249
Actually, that's another reason
why I came by.

17:13.293 --> 17:15.860
♪♪

17:15.904 --> 17:18.776
Well, this is
my last two minutes,

17:18.820 --> 17:22.432
so I just wanted to say
that I have loved

17:22.476 --> 17:25.131
being here
these past few weeks.

17:25.174 --> 17:29.178
Maybe that love
wasn't exactly mutual.

17:29.222 --> 17:31.572
At least one of you thinks
that I sound like

17:31.615 --> 17:36.011
"a cartoon baby turtle,
who is both bossy

17:36.055 --> 17:38.318
and afraid
to come out of her shell."

17:38.361 --> 17:40.581
Aw, thanks so much
for sending that in.

17:40.624 --> 17:42.539
[ Inhales deeply ]

17:42.583 --> 17:45.281
The truth is, as a therapist,

17:45.325 --> 17:48.589
I am trained to leave
my personal life out of the job.

17:48.632 --> 17:50.243
Maybe that was a mistake.

17:50.286 --> 17:52.854
I mean, this show
is not therapy.

17:55.509 --> 17:57.641
Trina,
if you are still listening,

17:57.685 --> 18:01.428
there's something that I wish
I had said to you this morning.

18:01.471 --> 18:05.171
I know exactly
what you're going through.

18:05.214 --> 18:08.174
I was too afraid to tell
my friends about my diagnosis

18:08.217 --> 18:09.566
at first, too.

18:09.610 --> 18:12.526
And it wasn't until I joined
my support group

18:12.569 --> 18:16.530
that I found the courage
to tell people.

18:16.573 --> 18:18.445
Not that the group
fixed everything.

18:18.488 --> 18:19.837
I mean,
I was still going through

18:19.881 --> 18:22.971
all of the stages
of grief and hope

18:23.014 --> 18:25.060
and, you know, everything
in between...

18:25.104 --> 18:30.021
[Inhales deeply]
but it gave me a connection

18:30.065 --> 18:32.894
to other people who knew
what I was going through.

18:32.937 --> 18:35.592
In fact,
I even connected with one of

18:35.636 --> 18:38.160
the male breast cancer survivors
in the church bathroom.

18:38.204 --> 18:39.857
[ Chuckles ]

18:39.901 --> 18:44.035
Not the point.
Um, the point is,

18:44.079 --> 18:46.386
maybe with the people
in that group,

18:46.429 --> 18:49.040
you, like me,

18:49.084 --> 18:52.435
can find exactly
what you need.

18:52.479 --> 18:55.612
♪♪

18:55.656 --> 18:58.267
Man:
15 seconds, Maggie.

18:58.311 --> 19:03.490
And...I'm afraid
my time has run out.

19:03.533 --> 19:07.189
So [sighs]
this is Dr. Maggie Bloom,

19:07.233 --> 19:10.018
saying...goodbye.

19:11.237 --> 19:12.194
[ Clicks ]

19:12.238 --> 19:19.201
♪♪

19:19.245 --> 19:28.210
♪♪

19:28.254 --> 19:31.126
[ Laughs ]

19:31.170 --> 19:33.346
Okay, how did you know
that my favorite dish

19:33.389 --> 19:35.391
is chicken Parmesan?

19:35.435 --> 19:38.220
I, uh, got some intel
from Gina.

19:38.264 --> 19:40.527
It's only fair, since
you're my number one fan.

19:40.570 --> 19:42.964
I think the manager
at Crocodilze

19:43.007 --> 19:44.052
is your number one fan.

19:44.095 --> 19:45.532
Hmm.
Come on.
Look at this.

19:45.575 --> 19:46.924
[ Laughs ]
Crazy.

19:46.968 --> 19:48.970
Yeah. I'm just sorry Gina
has to work for that guy.

19:49.013 --> 19:50.450
Uh, yeah.
Mm.

19:50.493 --> 19:53.148
Although, they make
a mean mac and cheese.

19:53.192 --> 19:54.671
Oh, if you think
that is good,

19:54.715 --> 19:56.543
I have to take you to
Aunty Melva's on the east side.

19:56.586 --> 19:57.979
Oh, I heard about
that place.

19:58.022 --> 19:59.894
They got five church fans
for their peach cobbler.

19:59.937 --> 20:01.200
Church fans?

20:01.243 --> 20:03.767
Is that like stars?

20:03.811 --> 20:05.508
I've never seen that
on Yelp.

20:05.552 --> 20:07.510
It's Black Yelp, baby.

20:07.554 --> 20:10.383
[ Both laugh ]

20:10.426 --> 20:12.515
Okay, how about
this weekend?

20:12.559 --> 20:14.300
Ugh.
I wish I could.

20:14.343 --> 20:16.606
I found out why
they canceled my scenes today.

20:16.650 --> 20:17.999
The production
is moving to Miami.

20:18.042 --> 20:19.435
Miami? When?

20:19.479 --> 20:21.568
I'm flying out tomorrow.

20:21.611 --> 20:23.570
Oh.

20:23.613 --> 20:25.093
But we can get
that peach cobbler

20:25.136 --> 20:26.660
the next time I'm in town.

20:26.703 --> 20:29.184
Yeah.
Yeah, great.

20:29.228 --> 20:30.229
Mm.

20:30.272 --> 20:32.622
It's just...

20:32.666 --> 20:35.190
I'm really sad
you're leaving.

20:35.234 --> 20:37.236
You know?

20:37.279 --> 20:38.367
Me too.

20:38.411 --> 20:41.588
♪♪

20:41.631 --> 20:44.243
[ Door opens ]

20:44.286 --> 20:46.593
Uh, M-Mom.

20:46.636 --> 20:48.116
Is, uh --
Is everything okay?

20:48.159 --> 20:49.422
Mm-hmm.

20:49.465 --> 20:51.337
[ Speaking Korean ]

20:51.380 --> 20:54.731
Oh. Sorry,
goggle emergency.
Oh.

20:54.775 --> 20:59.780
Uh, Shanice, this is my mom,
Joo Hee.

20:59.823 --> 21:00.868
It's a pleasure
to meet you.

21:03.131 --> 21:04.872
I'll go, uh,
get the goggles.

21:04.915 --> 21:06.700
Be right back.

21:09.790 --> 21:11.618
[ Chuckles ]

21:11.661 --> 21:13.359
[ Rhythmic knock on door ]

21:13.402 --> 21:14.316
[ Door opens ]

21:15.404 --> 21:16.362
Oh, hey.
What are you doing here?

21:16.405 --> 21:18.233
Hey.

21:19.234 --> 21:20.975
Can we talk?

21:21.018 --> 21:23.412
Actually, I gotta get this gift
over to Milo for Danny

21:23.456 --> 21:25.458
before he turns into
a pumpkin.

21:25.501 --> 21:26.937
It's about Peter.

21:26.981 --> 21:30.463
♪♪

21:30.506 --> 21:32.508
Georgia:
Christopher?

21:32.552 --> 21:33.944
♪♪

21:33.988 --> 21:35.816
[ Door opens ]

21:35.859 --> 21:37.513
There you are.

21:37.557 --> 21:39.776
♪♪

21:39.820 --> 21:41.169
What are you doing
in here?

21:41.212 --> 21:42.388
You remember freshman year,

21:42.431 --> 21:44.564
I went to surprise Layla
at school?

21:44.607 --> 21:47.349
I wanted to
take her out to dinner.

21:47.393 --> 21:48.785
Yeah.

21:48.829 --> 21:51.135
When she opened
her dorm room door...

21:53.137 --> 21:56.053
...I could tell
that she'd been crying.

21:56.097 --> 21:57.359
I didn't push.

21:57.403 --> 21:59.056
I didn't ask.

21:59.100 --> 22:00.841
I didn't do anything.

22:00.884 --> 22:02.756
♪♪

22:02.799 --> 22:06.716
I have a million
of those moments.

22:06.760 --> 22:09.240
Knowing I could've
done more.

22:09.284 --> 22:10.329
Georgia...

22:10.372 --> 22:16.291
♪♪

22:16.335 --> 22:17.510
I did something.

22:19.250 --> 22:21.557
The other night,
I went over to Peter's.

22:21.601 --> 22:23.342
♪ Finalmente...♪

22:23.385 --> 22:27.128
We just went over there
to scare him...

22:27.171 --> 22:29.609
So that he would never
hurt anyone again.

22:29.652 --> 22:30.958
♪ ...ci redimeremmo♪

22:31.001 --> 22:33.917
But something in me
snapped.

22:33.961 --> 22:37.181
♪♪

22:37.225 --> 22:40.489
♪ Finalmente...♪

22:40.533 --> 22:41.925
It wasn't supposed to go
that way.

22:41.969 --> 22:46.974
♪ ...il dolore...♪

22:47.017 --> 22:49.280
And I needed you
to hear that from me.

22:49.324 --> 22:51.631
♪ ...finira'♪

22:51.674 --> 22:53.415
I don't know
what happens next.

22:53.459 --> 22:55.025
♪♪

22:55.069 --> 22:58.942
And I won't blame you
if you never forgive me.

22:58.986 --> 23:02.424
Just know that everything I did,
I did for Layla.

23:02.468 --> 23:03.773
♪♪

23:03.817 --> 23:11.607
♪ E saremo...♪

23:11.651 --> 23:13.087
I know.

23:13.130 --> 23:16.046
♪♪

23:16.090 --> 23:17.396
I know.

23:17.439 --> 23:21.356
♪ ...in pace♪

23:21.400 --> 23:23.619
I know this is
a lot to take in.

23:23.663 --> 23:25.360
I was just trying to
protect you.No.

23:25.404 --> 23:27.406
♪♪

23:27.449 --> 23:30.278
No, what you did
had nothing to do with me.

23:30.321 --> 23:33.020
You went there that night
because you felt guilty --

23:33.063 --> 23:34.978
because you always need to be
this hero.

23:35.022 --> 23:36.458
No, this...Soph, that's not true.

23:36.502 --> 23:37.807
I --
Listen to me!

23:39.635 --> 23:42.508
I was dealing with it!

23:42.551 --> 23:45.554
I-I found the courage
to go to the police

23:45.598 --> 23:48.078
and do it the right way.

23:48.122 --> 23:51.430
God, then -- then -- and then,
when that didn't work out,

23:51.473 --> 23:54.694
I was the one who figured out
how to tell my story anyway.

23:54.737 --> 23:56.130
I know.
You were so brave.

23:56.173 --> 23:58.480
It was amazing, and he's
so scared of that podcast.

23:58.524 --> 23:59.829
You should've seen his face.

23:59.873 --> 24:02.832
What do you mean?
You -- You saw him?

24:02.876 --> 24:07.054
♪♪

24:07.097 --> 24:08.229
Tell me.

24:08.272 --> 24:11.058
♪♪

24:11.101 --> 24:13.495
When he woke up,
he called me.

24:13.539 --> 24:15.279
He asked me
to go and see him.

24:15.323 --> 24:16.629
Because he knows.

24:16.672 --> 24:18.065
He knows that
it was me and Christopher.

24:18.108 --> 24:20.676
So -- So, I went.

24:20.720 --> 24:22.112
♪♪

24:22.156 --> 24:24.027
He wanted me to get you
to take the podcast down

24:24.071 --> 24:26.813
in exchange
for his silence.

24:26.856 --> 24:28.815
Obviously,
that's not gonna happen.

24:28.858 --> 24:31.208
♪♪

24:31.252 --> 24:34.385
I-I can't even believe this.

24:34.429 --> 24:39.086
♪♪

24:39.129 --> 24:41.218
I mean, all you do
is just make my life harder.

24:41.262 --> 24:43.351
♪♪

24:43.394 --> 24:46.615
The last thing I ever want to do
in this world is hurt you.

24:46.659 --> 24:52.752
♪♪

24:52.795 --> 24:54.362
It's too late for that.

24:54.405 --> 24:57.670
♪♪

25:06.679 --> 25:08.158
Oh. I know.

25:08.202 --> 25:10.030
I'm done.[ Door closes ]

25:10.073 --> 25:11.727
Uh, don't worry.
I'll make sure to

25:11.771 --> 25:13.903
leave my ID badge
on the desk,

25:13.947 --> 25:15.035
even though this
is the best picture

25:15.078 --> 25:16.819
anyone's taken of me
in years.

25:16.863 --> 25:18.125
Actually,
can I keep this?

25:18.168 --> 25:19.779
Sure.

25:19.822 --> 25:21.084
You're gonna need it
on Monday.

25:21.128 --> 25:22.346
♪♪

25:22.390 --> 25:24.174
Monday?

25:24.218 --> 25:25.349
Does that mean
I'm coming back?

25:25.393 --> 25:27.177
Yeah.

25:27.221 --> 25:29.789
I have a feeling after today,
your numbers are gonna go up.

25:29.832 --> 25:32.313
But it is your job
to keep them up.

25:32.356 --> 25:33.923
Oh, my gosh.

25:33.967 --> 25:35.403
Thank you.

25:35.446 --> 25:38.101
[ Laughs ]
I don't know what to say.

25:38.145 --> 25:39.625
♪♪

25:39.668 --> 25:41.714
How long have you been
in remission?

25:41.757 --> 25:43.411
♪♪

25:43.454 --> 25:45.761
Uh, 18 months.

25:45.805 --> 25:48.155
Four years, last March.

25:48.198 --> 25:50.287
♪♪

25:50.331 --> 25:54.204
And, uh, things got
a little messy for me, too.

25:55.641 --> 26:00.036
Before, um, I had this job,
I was Nick's producer.

26:00.080 --> 26:04.040
And then I was his, uh,
well, something else.

26:04.911 --> 26:07.043
We had a lot of fun.

26:07.087 --> 26:08.610
Actually, we had fun
right there on that desk.

26:08.654 --> 26:10.960
[ Chuckles ]
Mm.

26:11.004 --> 26:13.180
And then I, um,
was offered the promotion

26:13.223 --> 26:19.142
to station manager,
and when I told Nick...

26:19.186 --> 26:21.710
he wanted to take me to
Nantucket to celebrate,

26:21.754 --> 26:26.889
but I-I freaked out
about h-him seeing me naked.

26:28.543 --> 26:33.156
We'd had office quickies,
but he had never seen my scars.

26:33.200 --> 26:34.984
No one had.

26:35.028 --> 26:38.466
And I just --
I couldn't risk it.

26:38.509 --> 26:42.644
I told him that corporate
was making me choose,

26:42.688 --> 26:46.517
but I didn't pick this job
over Nick.

26:46.561 --> 26:48.476
I lied to him
because I was scared.

26:48.519 --> 26:51.566
♪♪

26:51.610 --> 26:53.437
I'm sorry.
That was probably too much.

26:53.481 --> 26:56.353
No. It wasn't.

26:56.397 --> 26:57.790
And I get it.
Believe me.

26:57.833 --> 27:00.096
I-I really do.

27:00.140 --> 27:01.271
I thought you would.

27:02.969 --> 27:05.232
About what I told you
happened on the desk --

27:05.275 --> 27:08.757
please don't report me
to Rachel from HR.

27:08.801 --> 27:11.151
[ Chuckles ]Not to be confused with...

27:11.194 --> 27:13.283
Rachel Frumaychar.Rachel Frumaychar.
[ Chuckles ]

27:13.327 --> 27:21.074
♪♪

27:21.117 --> 27:23.076
[ Door closes ]

27:23.119 --> 27:24.555
[ Faucet running ]

27:26.775 --> 27:28.429
Thank you.

27:35.610 --> 27:37.960
Can I ask you something?

27:38.004 --> 27:40.310
Sure.

27:40.354 --> 27:42.008
Before your mom came in,

27:42.051 --> 27:44.750
I kind of felt like
we were having a moment.

27:46.273 --> 27:47.796
I don't know
what you mean.

27:54.498 --> 27:56.849
Theo showed up at
our hotel room the other night

27:56.892 --> 28:00.156
to tell Kiana how hew felt.

28:00.200 --> 28:02.637
It was a very brave move.

28:04.421 --> 28:07.816
Who does he get that from?

28:10.906 --> 28:14.693
Shanice, I was married to a man
for 12 years.

28:14.736 --> 28:17.521
And I was married to one
for 14.

28:17.565 --> 28:19.567
It doesn't mean
you can't have feelings for me.

28:22.135 --> 28:25.051
I just don't want you
to limit yourself

28:25.094 --> 28:28.228
because you think
it's what you "should" do.

28:28.271 --> 28:31.753
But isn't that
what you're doing?

28:31.797 --> 28:33.494
I mean, you said you haven't
told your parents

28:33.537 --> 28:34.843
about your private life,

28:34.887 --> 28:37.716
and you definitely
don't tell the world.

28:37.759 --> 28:40.196
It's different for me.
[ Scoffs lightly ]

28:40.240 --> 28:42.111
I don't know.

28:42.155 --> 28:44.810
Seems pretty similar.

28:44.853 --> 28:48.509
You're talking
about privacy.

28:48.552 --> 28:50.990
I'm talking
about feelings.

28:51.033 --> 28:55.124
♪♪

28:55.168 --> 28:58.084
Maybe I should go.

29:00.477 --> 29:02.001
[ Breathes sharply ]

29:02.044 --> 29:06.440
♪♪

29:09.878 --> 29:12.054
[ Faucet runs, turns off ]

29:12.098 --> 29:13.229
♪♪

29:13.273 --> 29:15.057
[ Boot zipping ]

29:15.101 --> 29:17.364
♪♪

29:17.407 --> 29:19.018
[ Sighs lightly ]

29:19.061 --> 29:20.410
I'm sorry.

29:21.934 --> 29:25.285
It must be
incredibly complicated for you,

29:25.328 --> 29:27.678
but it is for me, too.

29:29.332 --> 29:34.250
Ever since you came into
my life, I've been so confused.

29:34.294 --> 29:37.601
I've been feeling things I never
thought I would before.

29:37.645 --> 29:40.082
♪♪

29:40.126 --> 29:43.085
[ Sighs ]
Give yourself permission

29:43.129 --> 29:46.393
to feel
whatever you want.

29:46.436 --> 29:49.962
But I'm scared.

29:50.005 --> 29:56.098
I don't even know h--
I don't even know how to begin.

29:56.142 --> 29:58.318
I mean, you were there
for Never Have I Ever,

29:58.361 --> 30:02.365
and I've never even
kissed a woman before.

30:02.409 --> 30:11.157
♪♪

30:11.200 --> 30:20.209
♪♪

30:20.253 --> 30:22.211
Now you have.

30:22.255 --> 30:24.344
[ Chuckles ]

30:24.387 --> 30:26.520
Goodbye, Katherine.

30:26.563 --> 30:29.697
♪♪

30:29.740 --> 30:31.046
[ Door creaks ]

30:31.090 --> 30:32.874
[ Door closes ]

30:32.918 --> 30:34.745
♪♪

30:38.924 --> 30:41.448
Oh, Gina, you shoulda seen it.
People stayed for hours.

30:41.491 --> 30:43.015
This one man showed me
a scar on his face

30:43.058 --> 30:44.451
from marching
in Little Rock.

30:44.494 --> 30:45.800
That's amazing.

30:45.844 --> 30:46.932
I wish
I could've been there.

30:46.975 --> 30:48.411
This one woman,
she's a teacher.

30:48.455 --> 30:50.239
She wants me to show my movie
to her students,

30:50.283 --> 30:52.546
and, you know, I think
that's what I want to do.

30:52.589 --> 30:54.243
I want to just take
my film on the road

30:54.287 --> 30:55.375
and show it wherever I can.

30:55.418 --> 30:56.898
What about Paragon Plus?

30:56.942 --> 30:58.552
Won't they have
a problem with that?

30:58.595 --> 31:00.032
Well, how would
they find out?

31:00.075 --> 31:01.381
Hmm? I mean, if I --

31:01.424 --> 31:03.818
if I keep it to
the churches and the schools,

31:03.862 --> 31:05.385
I really think
I could do this.

31:05.428 --> 31:08.692
Well, I have some news,
too.

31:08.736 --> 31:11.043
Shanice dropped by Crocodilze
today.

31:11.086 --> 31:13.567
She pulled some strings, got me
a catering gig on her set.

31:13.610 --> 31:15.786
Gina, that's incredible!

31:15.830 --> 31:17.745
Yeah. It is.

31:17.788 --> 31:20.487
Except production's
moving to Miami.

31:20.530 --> 31:23.055
For like three months,
and I'd have to leave...

31:23.098 --> 31:25.057
really soon.

31:25.100 --> 31:27.755
[ Horn honks in distance,
indistinct conversations ]

31:27.798 --> 31:28.930
You have to do this.

31:28.974 --> 31:31.541
You mean that?

31:31.585 --> 31:32.847
Really?

31:32.891 --> 31:33.935
You get to make
the food you want,

31:33.979 --> 31:35.284
sip mai tais on the beach.[ Laughs ]

31:35.328 --> 31:36.807
We don't have to look after
Tyrell right now.

31:36.851 --> 31:39.941
This is a once-in-a-lifetime
opportunity.

31:39.985 --> 31:41.551
If you want my blessing,
I've been in church all day,

31:41.595 --> 31:42.639
so just consider that done.

31:42.683 --> 31:44.293
[ Laughs ]

31:44.337 --> 31:46.339
Mm.

31:46.382 --> 31:48.819
We've never even spent
more than a few nights apart.

31:48.863 --> 31:49.690
We'll sext.

31:50.996 --> 31:52.301
I've always wanted to
try that.

31:52.345 --> 31:54.782
Oh, we've sexted.

31:54.825 --> 31:55.957
Don't you remember
you sent me

31:56.001 --> 31:57.785
the picture of you
vacuuming?

31:57.828 --> 31:59.656
Oh, vacuuming?
[ Scoffs ]
[ Laughs ]

31:59.700 --> 32:01.702
Wait 'til you see me
load the dishwasher

32:01.745 --> 32:03.269
in my wide stance.[ Both laugh ]

32:03.312 --> 32:05.924
♪♪

32:05.967 --> 32:07.969
[ Chuckles ]

32:08.013 --> 32:09.231
Oh.
Oh! Sorry.

32:09.275 --> 32:10.885
I was just trying to
get a cup of coffee.

32:10.929 --> 32:12.974
Well, in that case --
[clears throat]

32:13.018 --> 32:14.758
Welcome to Starbucks.
May I take your order?

32:14.802 --> 32:17.500
Oh. Uh --
Uh, yeah, I'll have a,

32:17.544 --> 32:20.068
um, oh, decaf --
Ew.

32:20.112 --> 32:21.809
Half-caf?Better.

32:21.852 --> 32:24.203
Hazelnut coffee
with hazelnut creamer.

32:24.246 --> 32:26.335
So, basically, you don't like
the taste of coffee

32:26.379 --> 32:27.815
or the caffeine
that it offers.

32:27.858 --> 32:29.034
Got it.
[ Chuckles ]

32:29.077 --> 32:31.645
No, I love the caffeine.
I need the caffeine.

32:31.688 --> 32:33.603
Just, uh, not this late
in the afternoon.

32:33.647 --> 32:35.344
Would you have a scoop
of ice cream in your coffee

32:35.388 --> 32:36.606
if it was
socially acceptable?

32:36.650 --> 32:37.999
It is socially acceptable.

32:38.043 --> 32:39.696
It's called an affogato.

32:39.740 --> 32:41.568
Yes, and definitely
fact check

32:41.611 --> 32:43.222
when people are trying to
flirt with you.

32:43.265 --> 32:44.832
Okay. Okay.

32:44.875 --> 32:46.660
I am gonna need a name
for this order.

32:46.703 --> 32:48.705
[ Chuckles ]
Uh, Maggie.

32:48.749 --> 32:50.925
Okay. Mm-hmm.
[ Chuckles ]

32:50.969 --> 32:52.883
And a phone number,
please?

32:52.927 --> 32:55.016
[ Chuckles ] Well,
that has to be

32:55.060 --> 32:56.757
against company policy.

32:56.800 --> 32:58.367
I'm not really
committed to my job.

32:58.411 --> 32:59.978
So, you know...

33:01.240 --> 33:02.371
Alright,
let me write it.

33:02.415 --> 33:03.807
I saw how you wrote
"Muggie."

33:03.851 --> 33:05.157
It's not my penmanship.

33:05.200 --> 33:06.723
I just really think you look
more like a Muggie.

33:06.767 --> 33:09.335
[ Chuckles ]
Okay.

33:09.378 --> 33:10.684
Wait, if I give this
to you,

33:10.727 --> 33:12.033
I'm not gonna have
any coffee.

33:12.077 --> 33:14.035
Yeah, that's right.
Apparently, you hate coffee,

33:14.079 --> 33:15.906
so I'm gonna take you out
for an ice cream sundae.

33:15.950 --> 33:17.734
Oh, really?
Yeah. Mm-hmm.

33:17.778 --> 33:18.997
I'm gonna call you later
and set it up.

33:19.040 --> 33:20.868
[ Chuckling ] Okay.
Okay.

33:20.911 --> 33:23.436
Uh, don't do that
"wait four days" thing, either,

33:23.479 --> 33:25.525
'cause I take
my ice cream very seriously.

33:25.568 --> 33:27.701
Okay.
See you later, Muggie.

33:27.744 --> 33:29.137
Mr. Lamoureux.Yeah?

33:29.181 --> 33:30.965
Mr. Lamoureux,
I'm such a huge Bruins fan.

33:31.009 --> 33:32.836
Can I get a photo?Only if I can be in it.

33:32.880 --> 33:34.229
Awesome.
Let's go, buddy.

33:34.273 --> 33:35.535
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:35.578 --> 33:36.840
[ Shutter clicks ]

33:36.884 --> 33:38.016
[ Conversations continue ]

33:38.059 --> 33:39.104
[ Elevator bell dings ]

33:40.801 --> 33:42.977
Sophie, what's going on?[ Sighs ]

33:43.021 --> 33:45.327
Talk to me.

33:45.371 --> 33:46.937
[ Voice breaking ]
It's Gary.

33:46.981 --> 33:48.156
What?
[ Sniffles ]

33:49.114 --> 33:50.506
[ Video game beeping ]

33:50.550 --> 33:51.638
What do you think?

33:53.988 --> 33:56.817
Rent's paid for
the next six months.

33:56.860 --> 34:01.082
And one more thing --
the lease is in my name.

34:01.126 --> 34:03.171
So, he won't be able to
find us.

34:03.215 --> 34:05.739
You deserve a fresh start.

34:05.782 --> 34:07.523
We both do.

34:07.567 --> 34:10.004
I can't believe
you would do this for me.

34:10.048 --> 34:11.832
After everything
I've put you through.

34:11.875 --> 34:13.703
Well, I'm not just
doing it for you.

34:13.747 --> 34:15.227
♪♪

34:15.270 --> 34:19.100
I...can't keep holding on
to my anger.

34:19.144 --> 34:20.362
♪♪

34:20.406 --> 34:23.017
I need to let it go.

34:23.061 --> 34:24.540
So that's what I'm doing.

34:24.584 --> 34:26.368
♪♪

34:26.412 --> 34:28.631
Where will you live?

34:28.675 --> 34:30.546
I'm gonna stay
where I am for now.

34:30.590 --> 34:32.853
♪♪

34:32.896 --> 34:35.247
I have a friend
who needs me.

34:35.290 --> 34:38.163
♪♪

34:38.206 --> 34:40.078
[ Smooches ]

34:40.121 --> 34:41.296
♪♪

34:41.340 --> 34:43.864
[ Crying ]
Thank you.

34:43.907 --> 34:52.177
♪♪

34:52.220 --> 34:54.135
[ Pounding on door ]

34:54.179 --> 34:56.094
♪♪

34:56.137 --> 34:57.312
[ Sighs ]

34:57.356 --> 35:07.279
♪♪

35:07.322 --> 35:08.758
[ Sighs ]

35:12.197 --> 35:13.981
What are you doing here,
Bloom?

35:14.024 --> 35:15.635
Sophie told me
what you did.

35:18.203 --> 35:19.987
[ Sighs ]

35:21.858 --> 35:23.469
[ Sighs ]

35:23.512 --> 35:24.774
How's she doing?

35:24.818 --> 35:26.994
[ Door closes ]Not great.

35:27.037 --> 35:28.430
Well, if you're here to
lecture me, don't bother,

35:28.474 --> 35:30.867
because I'm actually pretty good
at that myself.

35:30.911 --> 35:32.608
I'm here to see
if you're okay.

35:36.003 --> 35:37.831
Darcy broke up with me.

35:39.963 --> 35:41.791
Gary, I'm so sorry.

35:41.835 --> 35:44.577
She was right,
after what I did.

35:45.708 --> 35:47.710
It was never
supposed to go that far.

35:47.754 --> 35:49.321
I know.
I didn't hurt him.

35:49.364 --> 35:50.974
I swear.
I know.

35:51.018 --> 35:52.411
I know you.

35:52.454 --> 35:53.716
You're not capable
of that.

35:55.370 --> 35:59.853
But I do think it would be good
for you to talk to someone.

35:59.896 --> 36:00.854
You know, someone
who could help you

36:00.897 --> 36:02.812
understand
why you did this.

36:02.856 --> 36:04.684
Well, I'll have
plenty of time.

36:04.727 --> 36:07.556
Peter's going to the cops
and I'm going to jail.

36:07.600 --> 36:09.297
[ Sighs ]
Maybe not.

36:09.341 --> 36:12.866
Sophie asked me
to take her podcast down.What?

36:12.909 --> 36:15.738
Yeah, she said Peter offered you
some kind of deal?

36:15.782 --> 36:18.611
No. No. I did not
want her to do that.

36:18.654 --> 36:21.483
It's not up to you. Gary,
please don't go over there.[ Door opens ]

36:21.527 --> 36:23.529
I'm sorry.
I gotta go.

36:23.572 --> 36:24.704
[ Door closes ][ Sighs ]

36:29.187 --> 36:31.580
Hey.

36:31.624 --> 36:33.234
Did you talk to Rome?I did.

36:33.278 --> 36:35.018
He's totally on board.[ Gasps ]

36:35.062 --> 36:36.890
So, you're going to Miami?Mm-hmm.

36:36.933 --> 36:39.327
That's amazing.

36:39.371 --> 36:40.589
When do you leave?

36:40.633 --> 36:42.374
Tomorrow morning.

36:42.417 --> 36:43.853
I'm about to quit.

36:43.897 --> 36:45.855
But I want to quit
for two.

36:47.292 --> 36:48.815
Come with me.

36:48.858 --> 36:52.732
Regina [scoffs]
it's not that easy for me.

36:52.775 --> 36:55.343
I have a record.
I-I have to be more careful.

36:55.387 --> 36:57.215
Okay, but just
think about it.

36:57.258 --> 36:59.217
This is a good move.

36:59.260 --> 37:00.783
We make a great team.

37:00.827 --> 37:02.742
We'd be our own bosses.

37:02.785 --> 37:06.224
I remember you saying how
you wanted that so badly.

37:06.267 --> 37:08.269
You'd get your foot in the door
with an A-list producer.

37:08.313 --> 37:11.446
After that, there'd be so many
other opportunities.

37:13.187 --> 37:14.971
We could put the ketchup
wherever we want?

37:15.015 --> 37:17.191
And the mustard,
and the mayonnaise,

37:17.235 --> 37:19.324
and we might even get crazy
with the cinnamon.
Yes!

37:19.367 --> 37:21.108
[ Both laugh ]

37:21.151 --> 37:22.892
Wait, wait, why are you putting
your chef's jacket back on?

37:22.936 --> 37:24.372
'Cause I want to do
that thing

37:24.416 --> 37:26.156
where you take it off
dramatically when you quit.

37:26.200 --> 37:27.462
Yes.
I want to do that, too.

37:27.506 --> 37:30.596
♪♪

37:30.639 --> 37:32.293
[ Laptop keys clacking ]

37:32.337 --> 37:33.425
[ Laptop chimes ]

37:35.905 --> 37:37.080
[ Mouse clicking ]

37:37.124 --> 37:44.523
♪♪

37:44.566 --> 37:51.965
♪♪

37:52.008 --> 37:59.407
♪♪

37:59.451 --> 38:01.061
Okay, Tyrell, we miss you.

38:01.104 --> 38:02.280
Tyrell: Miss you, too.
Good luck in Miami.

38:02.323 --> 38:04.282
Gina,
you're gonna crush it.

38:04.325 --> 38:06.284
Thanks. [ Chuckles ]
Give your mom our best.

38:06.327 --> 38:07.459
And let her know she's got
family over here

38:07.502 --> 38:08.373
if she needs anything.
Alright?

38:08.416 --> 38:09.635
We love you.
Bye.

38:09.678 --> 38:11.376
Bye.
Bye.

38:11.419 --> 38:12.464
[ Cellphone beeps ]

38:12.507 --> 38:14.944
Okay.
There's no time to get sad.

38:14.988 --> 38:16.250
Tyrell's gonna be back
in a couple of months,

38:16.294 --> 38:17.686
and you've got to
finish packing.

38:18.992 --> 38:20.776
I don't know.

38:20.820 --> 38:22.387
This is all
happening so fast.

38:22.430 --> 38:24.693
Is it happening too fast?

38:24.737 --> 38:26.913
You have to do this.

38:26.956 --> 38:28.871
Yeah, you're right.

38:28.915 --> 38:30.220
You're right.

38:30.264 --> 38:32.919
Let's see.
I've packed clothes,

38:32.962 --> 38:36.009
toiletries,
my chef's knives,

38:36.052 --> 38:36.705
something to read
on the plane --

38:36.749 --> 38:38.707
I can't go.
Gina.

38:39.447 --> 38:42.232
Not until we say
a proper goodbye.

38:42.276 --> 38:44.365
♪♪

38:44.409 --> 38:46.672
May I see you on the bed,
please?

38:46.715 --> 38:49.239
Oh, so sexting won't start
until tomorrow?

38:49.283 --> 38:50.545
Mm-hmm.

38:50.589 --> 38:52.286
I'm not mad at that.Mm-hmm. Mm.

38:52.330 --> 38:58.771
♪♪

38:58.814 --> 39:00.555
Honey?

39:00.599 --> 39:02.209
I thought I'd order us
some dinner

39:02.252 --> 39:04.429
and try to make up for
all that bland hospital food.

39:08.781 --> 39:10.130
What's going on?

39:10.173 --> 39:12.045
That's what
I should've been asking you.

39:12.088 --> 39:13.089
[ Chuckling ] What?

39:14.439 --> 39:15.875
[ Sighs ]

39:15.918 --> 39:18.268
♪♪

39:18.312 --> 39:21.097
What happened
with Sophie Dixon?

39:21.141 --> 39:23.273
Uh, what --
what are you talking about?

39:23.317 --> 39:25.754
I listened to her podcast.

39:25.798 --> 39:27.669
She said that
you did things to her.

39:27.713 --> 39:29.149
♪♪

39:29.192 --> 39:30.933
Right here.

39:30.977 --> 39:33.588
None of the stuff
that she said is true.

39:33.632 --> 39:37.766
In fact, someone called me
and -- and she took it down.

39:37.810 --> 39:39.246
Because she's lying.

39:39.289 --> 39:41.944
When you were still in a coma,
I unlocked your phone.

39:41.988 --> 39:43.729
♪♪

39:43.772 --> 39:45.121
Do you know what I found?

39:45.165 --> 39:47.689
♪♪

39:47.733 --> 39:50.083
Nothing.

39:50.126 --> 39:52.825
[ Voice breaking ]
No pictures, no texts.

39:52.868 --> 39:56.437
No trace of your entire life
outside of us.

39:56.481 --> 39:58.831
Which is exactly
what someone would do

39:58.874 --> 40:00.920
if they had
something to hide.

40:00.963 --> 40:02.443
♪♪

40:02.487 --> 40:05.272
[ Voice breaking ]
Anna, I love you.

40:05.315 --> 40:07.187
We're done.

40:07.230 --> 40:10.146
And I'm gonna make sure
that you never teach again.

40:10.190 --> 40:14.194
♪♪

40:14.237 --> 40:15.891
Anna...

40:15.935 --> 40:18.372
♪♪

40:18.416 --> 40:21.201
Thanks so much, Soph.
Your timing was perfect.

40:21.244 --> 40:23.421
[ Chuckles ]
I'm so glad I could help.

40:23.464 --> 40:25.684
He looked crazy cute
in the beret.

40:25.727 --> 40:27.773
Yeah, he did.

40:27.816 --> 40:29.470
Are you okay?[ Door opens ]

40:29.514 --> 40:31.124
You sound weird.

40:31.864 --> 40:33.082
[ Door closes ]

40:33.126 --> 40:36.172
I'm fine.
Just go get some sleep.

40:36.216 --> 40:38.740
Okay. Good night.
I love you.

40:38.784 --> 40:39.915
Love you, too.

40:44.703 --> 40:46.052
Maggie told me
you were coming.

40:46.095 --> 40:48.533
I did not want you to
take the podcast down.

40:48.576 --> 40:50.273
You didn't have to
do that for me.

40:50.317 --> 40:51.710
Yeah, well,
I didn't do it for you.

40:51.753 --> 40:53.146
I did it for Layla's mom.

40:53.189 --> 40:55.061
♪♪

40:55.104 --> 40:56.366
She's already
lost her daughter.

40:56.410 --> 40:58.760
She doesn't need to lose
her husband, too.

40:58.804 --> 41:03.286
And if I hadn't gone over there
and asked for her diary,

41:03.330 --> 41:05.375
I mean, they wouldn't be
in this mess to begin with.

41:05.419 --> 41:08.161
It's not your fault.
It's my fault.

41:08.204 --> 41:10.032
You're right.
It is.

41:10.076 --> 41:14.994
♪♪

41:15.037 --> 41:16.517
Soph...

41:16.561 --> 41:18.388
If you really want
what's best for me,

41:18.432 --> 41:20.260
you'll stay away.

41:20.303 --> 41:21.217
For good.

41:21.261 --> 41:29.748
♪♪

